<header id="detail-header">
	<h1>The Patent Leather Kid</h1>
</header>

	<section id="film-detail-container">
		<img src="../static/images/m13.jpeg" alt="Film poster">

		<p><em>The Patent Leather Kid</em> is a silent drama film directed by Alfred Santell, starring Richard Barthelmess, Molly O&#39;Day, Lawford Davidson, Matthew Betz, and Arthur Stone.</p>

		<p>Alfred Santell and Richard A. Rowland produced the film.</p>

		<p>
			It was released by First National Pictures on August 15, 1927, with a runtime of 108 minutes.

			
				It had a budget of $850,000  and made $1.2 million at the box office.
				When adjusted for inflation in 2023, that's approximately equivalent to $14.7 million and $20.7 million, respectively.
			
		</p>

		<p>
			The film was written by Rupert Hughes and Winifred Dunn, with Arthur Edeson, Ralph Hammeras, and Alvin Knechtel overseeing cinematography and Cecil Copping composing the film's music. No information could be found on there being an official editor for the film.
		</p>

		<p><a href="https://archive.org/details/the-patent-leather-kid_1927">View an archived version of <em>The Patent Leather Kid</em>.</a></p>

		<p><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Patent_Leather_Kid">View the Wikipedia entry for <em>The Patent Leather Kid</em>.</a></p>

		<p><a href="../index.html">Return to the list</a> to select a different film.</p>
	</section>

